stylometry: @Risk takes several inputs and runs simulations (1000 interations) to show how the different inputs affect the desired output. When I run a simulation with 5 inputs, it simulates different scenarios for each and show the desired outcome by each and the data(standard deviation, mean, minimum, and miaximum) for each input. This is then used by the user to determine which input he/she will choose in order to solve the problem. For example; if the goal is maximum profit and the input that has maximum profit also has the highest standard deviation, it is up to the user to decide if that is really the best choice.
